<p>But the original comment plug-in:Disqus is a paid service, so I tried another popular comment tool:<a href="https://gitalk.github.io/">GiTalk</a>.Everything is fine until I met with â€œNot Foundâ€ Error when I deployed.</p>

<p><img src="./assets/img/posts/20220111/GiTalk_error.png" alt="not found error" /></p>

<p>The followings are the steps to solve this â€œNot Foundâ€ error when activating gitalk on your webpage:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Create a new github repo for comments storage</li>
</ul>

<p><img src="./assets/img/posts/20220111/create_new_repo_comment.png" alt="create comment repo" /></p>

<ul>
  <li>Enabling the â€œissuesâ€ of this repo,and activate the â€œissuesâ€ with first comment</li>
</ul>

<p><img src="./assets/img/posts/20220111/issues_enabled.png" alt="issues enabled" />
<img src="./assets/img/posts/20220111/create_first_comment.png" alt="first comment" /></p>

<ul>
  <li>Configure the OAuth Apps in Github Apps setting</li>
</ul>

<p><img src="./assets/img/posts/20220111/clientID_key.png" alt="app kid key" />
<img src="./assets/img/posts/20220111/set_OAuth.png" alt="set Oauth" /></p>

<ul>
  <li>Configure the â€œrepoâ€ of gitalk js code without â€œhttps://â€ prefix ,
just set it like this:  repo: blog-comments(repo name)</li>
</ul>

<p><img src="./assets/img/posts/20220111/set repo.png" alt="Set repo name" /></p>

<p>Finally, you can see the perfect GiTalk tool on your webpage.</p>

<p><img src="./assets/img/posts/20220111/correct_GiTalk.png" alt="enjoy" /></p>

<p>Enjoy GiTalk!</p>
